TYPE ERROR: Under-determined effect variable <e> in method 'speak' of interface 'Speak': the effect appears only in the method's return type, pinned by no argument, so a caller can instantiate it to <> and launder the real effect (a function typed pure would silently perform it). Use a concrete effect row (e.g. `<Stdout>`) or thread the effect through an argument (e.g. a callback `a -> <e> b`).
